<body class="dark:bg-teal-800 dark:text-gray-300">
  {{>header}}
  <main class='bg-color-two flex-grow flex'>
    <div class="mx-4 sm:mx-8 lg:mx-16 my-2 sm:my-6 lg:my-8 ">
      <h1 class="text-center text-xl sm:text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold">{{title}}</h1>
      <div class="leading-7 lg:text-xl lg:leading-loose">

        {{!-- Q&A --}}
        <p class="font-bold leading-loose">What is this webpage?</p>
        <p>This is a basic webpage that tells users about the weather in any location typed in the world. It
          uses data from <strong><a href="https://www.mapbox.com/" target="_blank"
            class='underline hover:text-colorT-three'>mapbox.com</a></strong> for geocoding and <strong><a href="https://weatherstack.com/"
            target="_blank" class='underline hover:text-colorT-three'>weatherstack.com</a></strong> for the API.</p>
        <br>
        <p class="font-bold leading-loose">How does it work?</p>
        <p>It is very simple. Click on the 'Weather' tab. On this page the user will find an input box which has a placeholder of Location, where
          he/she can type in the location they want. Click the 'Search' button beside the input box and
          voil√†!
        </p>
        <br>
        <p class="font-bold leading-loose">I followed the instructions, but got the weather information from
          some
          other
          place. What can I do?</p>
        <p>In cases like this, I suggest not to just type in the city name, try typing in the country's name as well.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

